  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">States-in-Waiting (2024), published by Cambridge University Press. Scholarly uptake (strength 0.6). Sustainability & policy relevance (strength 0.6).</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">States-in-Waiting was published by Cambridge University Press in 2024. It is part of the Global and International History series. Conceptually, the work connects to History and Geography.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">OpenAlex records 20 citations. Citations peaked in 2025 with 15 citing works. Notable citing venues include Comparative Studies of South Asia Africa and the Middle East, Cambridge University Press eBooks and Comparative Studies in Society and History. Inferred role: Scholarly uptake and Sustainability & policy relevance.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">669 recorded downloads via open-access infrastructure.  SDG alignment: Reduced inequalities.</p>",
